title: Ground News - SpaceX Falcon Heavy launches X-37B plane, one of the US military’s most fascinating secrets
text:
Summary by Ground News SpaceX 's hulking Falcon Heavy rocket returned to the skies Thursday evening. The rocket lifted off from NASA's Kennedy Space Center in Florida at 8:07 p.m. ET. It carried the military's X-37B space plane, which is uncrewed and operates autonomously. It is not clear, however, where the space plane is going. Share menu More

The rocket lifted off from NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida at 8:07 p.m. ET, carrying the military’s X-37B space plane — which is uncrewed and operates autonomously — to unprecedented altitudes.
